e^a = x
x = e^a = e^{-\ln(2)} = \dfrac12
\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} x^n = 2 \implies \dfrac1{1-x} = 2 \implies x = \dfrac12 \implies a = - \ln(2)
\sum_{n=0}^{\infty} e^{na} = \sum_{n=0}^{\infty} \dfrac1{2^n} = 2
